The bread was cold to the touch too. I should have known because the pizza box was not hot, as I walked two blocks home. Normally when you purchased a freshly made pizza pie, you can feel the heat radiating out of the pizza pie box, as you carry the pie. I called the Italian restaurant and told the manager this pie I just purchased from your restaurant is cold. The Manager told me to put the pizza pie in the oven WHAT!! It's Italian.  No, not like your "Italian" wife who's lived in New York for three generations.  The staff is Italian and speak Italian as their first language. The Spaghetti alla Carbonara was perhaps the best I've had in NYC - not salty and, as expected,  cooked with good pancetta - not bacon. First time here last night and man, I can stop talking about the pasta. We had the Rigatoni Funghi e Salsiccia which might have been the best pasta dish I have had. The pasta was cooked perfectly to al dente. Not too hard, not too soft, just the right amount texture. The pink sauce was so good we were dipping our bread in it by the end of the night! Man I want to go back already!  We also had the Brigante pizza which was a quality pie as well. Good tasty sauce. Great dough texture from the brick oven.  It’s a small spot in the seaport area. The seaport area is great to walk around and hang out. The place is a little loud and only has one bathroom. But actually the bathroom is one of the cutest well put to together bathrooms I have seen in NYC.  I would definitely go to this place if you are in the seaport or FIDI area! Get the pasta for sure!
